  "text": "OsDrAp1 was compared with DrAp1 from maize (mDrAp1), yeast (yDrAp1; [CITATION_1] , human (hDrAp1; [CITATION_2] , and Drosophila (dDrAp1; [CITATION_3] . H-Fold, histone-fold domain; QE, glutamine-and glutamate-rich domain; QA, glutamine-and alanine-rich domain; QP, glutamine-and proline-rich domain; aa, amino acids; B, basic amino acid stretch; RG, arginine-glycine repeat; A1 and A2, acidic amino acid-rich domain 1 and 2, respectively; P, proline-rich domain. lines containing either pAD::OsDr1 or pBD-OsDrAp1 alone had no ␤ -galactosidase activity. These data provide evidence that there is a physical interaction between OsDr1 and OsDrAp1 in yeast.",
